"'''Heart of Fire'''" is a three-page [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] written by [[John Ostrander]], pencilled and inked by [[Jan Duursema]] and colored by [[Dan Jackson]]. It appeared in three parts in ''[[Dark Horse Extra]]'' #35&ndash;#37.

==Plot summary==
[[File:VosAmersu-Heart.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Vos and Amersu]]

After the events of [[Star Wars: The Hunt for Aurra Sing|''Star Wars: Republic: The Hunt for Aurra Sing'']], [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Quinlan Vos/Legends|Quinlan Vos]] recovers in the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. While in the [[Jedi Temple meditation gardens|Meditation Garden]] Master Vos is interrupted by a young [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] Padawan. Quinlan recognizes the girl as [[Xiaan Amersu]], one whose Master died at the hands of [[Aurra Sing/Legends|Aurra Sing]]. Xiaan asks about [[Aayla Secura/Legends|Aayla Secura]] and offers Quinlan a shiny stone called the '[[Heart of Fire]]'. This stone was once his, but he gave it to Aayla, and she passed it to Xiaan. Now Xiaan gives it back to Quinlan. She insists that Quinlan reads the images of the stone, and he does&hellip;

==Continuity==
''Heart of Fire'' is reprinted in ''[[Star Wars Omnibus: Menace Revealed]]'', though it is stated to take place in approximately [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]]. It is therefore placed before ''The Hunt for Aurra Sing'' story arc in the Omnibus (itself dated approximately [[30 BBY/Legends|30 BBY]]), despite occurring after events in that arc's first issue.

